"Per EH 1909: 'not only became noted as a physician but was also prominent in the public affairs of the place.'"},{"role":"Member of Common Council","organization":"City of East Cambridge","location":"East Cambridge, Massachusetts"},{"role":"Alderman","organization":"City of East Cambridge","location":"East Cambridge, Massachusetts"},{"role":"Representative","organization":"Massachusetts General Court","location":"Boston, Massachusetts","notes":"Representative of East Cambridge in the Massachusetts General Court per EH 1909."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST043","relationship":"alumnus","years":"graduated 1819","institution_blurb":"Graduated Williams College 1819."},{"institution_id":"INST002","relationship":"alumnus","years":"graduated 1822","institution_blurb":"Graduated Harvard Medical School 1822."}],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["physician","harvard_graduate","politician"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"mentor_student","related_id":"H02763","display_label":"Studied medicine at East Cambridge; died of hospital disease, 1858","link_text":"Edward Hooker"},{"type":"mentor_student","related_id":"H02760","display_label":"Son who joined his practice; died New Year's Eve 1873","link_text":"Anson Parker Hooker"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Nephew died six weeks after son's birth, 1858","body":"His nephew Edward Hooker came to East Cambridge to study medicine after graduating Williams College in 1855, but died April 26, 1858 of disease contracted in hospital service — six weeks after Anson's youngest son Edward Dwight was born in the same East Cambridge household on March 17. The same spring brought both a birth and a death into the Hooker physician line."},{"number":2,"category":"politics","header":"Common Council to State House in one career","body":"Beyond his East Cambridge medical practice, Anson served successively on the Common Council, as Alderman, and as a Representative in the Massachusetts General Court — three ascending levels of civic office held while maintaining his practice from 1822 until his death in 1869. Harvard-trained physicians of his generation were expected to lead their communities as well as treat them."},{"number":3,"category":"legacy","header":"First of three consecutive Harvard physician generations, 1822","body":"Dr. Anson Hooker graduated Harvard Medical School in 1822 and built a Cambridge practice that his son Anson Parker inherited after Harvard M.D. 1855, and his grandson Edward Dwight carried on after Harvard M.D. 1884. Three consecutive Hooker physicians trained at Harvard across sixty-two years."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"anson-hooker-1799"},"H02761":{"id":"H02761","is_placeholder":true,"has_descendants_documented":false,"former_ids":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Charles Thompson Hooker","first_name":"Charles","middle_name":"Thompson","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[]},"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1834,"month":7,"day":21,"city":"East Cambridge","county":"Middlesex","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1872,"month":2,"day":9,"city":"Cambridge","county":"Middlesex","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"H01414","mother_id":"I01161"},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"number_of_marriages":0,"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"